==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Extenuation
<hw>Ex*ten`u*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>extenuatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>ext⟦eacute⟧nuation</ets>.]</ety>
<def>The act of extenuating or the state of being extenuated; the act of
making thin, slender, or lean, or of palliating; diminishing, or
lessening; palliation, as of a crime; mitigation, as of
punishment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To listen . . . to every <qex>extenuation</qex> of what is
evil.</q> <rj><qau>I. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Extenuator</ent>⟦br⟧
